A MOTORCYCLIST who died in an accident on the Isle of Lewis has been named by police.
Angus Chisholm, 42, from the Carloway area of the island, was killed in the one-vehicle crash at around 1.30pm yesterday.
The accident happened on the A858 just south of the junction leading to the village of Brue on the west coast of the island.
Police said a report will be sent to the procurator fiscal.
